**Memoryless Property of the Exponential Distribution.** Buses arrive as a Poisson process with rate $\lambda$ per hour (inter-arrivals $\sim\mathrm{Exp}(\lambda)$). You have already waited $t$ minutes. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item What is the probability you wait at least $s$ more minutes?

\item What is your expected additional waiting time?

\item State and explain the memoryless property.\end{enumerate}

**Geometric Distribution: Free-Throw Problem.** A basketball player makes each free throw independently with probability $p=0.7$. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item What is the probability the first miss occurs on exactly the 5th attempt?

\item Given the first 3 shots were made, what is the probability the first miss occurs after attempt 8?

\item What is the expected number of shots until the first miss?\end{enumerate}

**Poisson Process: Count in Overlapping Intervals.** Let $N(t)$ be a Poisson process with rate $\lambda$. Define: \[A = N(2)-N(1) \quad\text{(count in }[1,2]\text{)}, \qquad B = N(3)-N(1) \quad\text{(count in }[1,3]\text{)}\] \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item What are the distributions of $A$ and $B$ individually?

\item Are $A$ and $B$ independent? Explain.

\item Compute $\mathrm{Cov}(A,B)$.\end{enumerate}

**Expected Waiting Time for the $k$-th Poisson Event.** Events occur as a Poisson process with rate $\lambda=3$/hr. \begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph{*})]\item What is the distribution of the waiting time until the $k$-th event?

\item Compute the expected time and variance until the 4th event.

\item What is the probability exactly 5 events occur in the first 2 hours?\end{enumerate}
